# User Interface Patterns

## VS Code UI Components
- Use `vscode.window.showInputBox` for simple text input
- Use `vscode.window.showQuickPick` for selection from predefined options
- Use `vscode.window.showOpenDialog` for file selection
- Use `vscode.window.showInformationMessage` for success notifications
- Use `vscode.window.showErrorMessage` for error notifications

## User Interaction Flow
- Provide clear prompts and placeholders for all inputs
- Use emojis and descriptive labels to make options clear
- Offer multiple selection methods (browse, default, manual)
- Provide validation and feedback for user inputs

## File Selection Patterns
- Support browsing for files with appropriate filters
- Detect and suggest common file locations
- Validate file existence before processing
- Provide fallback options for file selection

## Configuration Interface
- Guide users through configuration step by step
- Offer intelligent defaults and suggestions
- Validate configurations before saving
- Provide clear feedback about saved settings

## Output and Logging
- Use `vscode.OutputChannel` for detailed logging
- Show relevant information in output channels
- Provide clear success/error messages
- Log all Docker commands for debugging

## Error Handling UI
- Show user-friendly error messages
- Log technical details to output channels
- Provide actionable error information
- Handle edge cases gracefully with clear feedback
